The ruling All Progressives Congress (APC) has adopted Hon. Femi Gbajabiamila as its candidate for the position of the Speaker of the House of Representatives in the 9th National Assembly. APC National Publicity Secretary, Lanre Issa-Onilu, in a terse message posted on the party’s WhatsApp platform on Tuesday night said the position was reached after an intensive deliberation with the APC’s House of Representatives members-elect at a dinner with President Muhammadu Buhari at the Banquet Hall of Aso Villa. Issa-Onilu said the Deputy Speaker position had been zoned to the North Central. Speaker: Gbajabiamila faces 8 contenders despite APC’s position Reps crisis: Lawmakers sue Dogara GBAJABIAMILA TO OYEGUN: PARTY MUST EXERT SUPREMACY ON DOGARA, OTHERS